    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhile exploring the vim.base64 functionality in Neovim, I noticed that the current documentation provides basic usage but lacks clear, real-world examples demonstrating how it can be used in practical scenarios.\n\nFor new users, especially those working with encoding/decoding data in plugins or scripts, it can be unclear how to apply this functionality effectively.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdd a dedicated section in the documentation with practical examples, such as:\n\nEncoding and decoding strings using vim.base64\nHandling binary data or file content\nExample use cases in plugin development\n\nExample (illustrative):\n\nlocal encoded = vim.base64.encode(\"hello\")\nprint(encoded)\n\nlocal decoded = vim.base64.decode(encoded)\nprint(decoded)",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
